    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Because codemirror will lose focus. And it triggers side effect of command mode, scolling, and all these annoying things.\n\nOf course, but you have already fixed that using `get_selected_cell()`. I mean given the current behavior in master, why do you want to avoid focus on the buttons of the toolbar? Particularly considering that a few milliseconds later, the focus will be moved to the selected cell, as it should.\n\n> We won't add tabindex, as keyboard user can use keyboard shortcut. Keyboard user will not \"navigate\" to button with keyboard.\n\nYes, but then you are not really addressing accessibility because screen readers navigate following the tabindex (or using the default browser behavior when no explicit tabindex is set) and obviously, shortcuts are not a solution in that case.\n"
