    "body": "From a quick test:\n- Simply entering command mode from edit mode still can trigger focus jump.\n- Clicking on the buttons in the toolbar doesn't cause a jump - it does fix that issue.\n\nBut...I think buttons should be buttons, not divs. Being forced on relying on button=div to fix this type of bug is not sustainable in the long run (just the accesibility issues alone, but also for writing semantic HTML). Plus, this doesn't really fix the underlying issues of focus that we have (some of the bugs remain and are unrelated to the buttons).\n"
